================================================================================
This is a README file of splitter.py 
================================================================================

splitter.py is a Python code with a purpose of splitting a rows of table into 2,
creating 2 new files of Training Data and Testing Data to be used in
data prediction using Neural Network.

Data suitable for this are:
* Files with comma separated value (.csv) or Ms Excel 2003-365 (.xlsx) extension
* Table or matrix data with regular rows and columns of uniform size
* Table with 1 line of header and then lines (or rows) of data
* Data with numerical or categorical values

Pre-Requisites
The code has been tested on numerous devices ranging in operating system, 
environment, and parameter. Before using the code, user have to install 
pre-requisite libraries: pandas, openpyxl, argparse, and colorama.

To install these libraries at once, execute the command on 
Windows Command Prompt (cmd) or Linux / MacOS Terminal :

    > pip install pandas openpyxl argparse colorama

and for more info, visit:
https://pandas.pydata.org/ 
https://openpyxl.readthedocs.io/ 
https://pypi.org/project/argparse/
https://pypi.org/project/colorama/

To use the code, simply run splitter.py with cmd or terminal
with the .xlsx or .csv file in the same directory as the .py file:

    > python splitter.py
    
                    ---> Training   
                   |                
     splitter -----|                
                   |                
                    ---> Testing    
    
    Python Program for Dividing Dataset into Training Data and Testing Data
    Enter the csv or xlsx file : 

and enter the file name and extension, e.g. data.xlsx or data.csv

The code will automatically split the data into the default value of 80% 
training data and 20% testing data. 

Optionally, for custom value of percentage, user can specify the desired 
percentage of training data by using additional argument when running the code:

    > python splitter.py --percent 70

where the value of percentage can vary from 0 to 100. After that, the process 
continues the same as before. This will split the data into a custom value 
of 70% training data and 30% testing data.

The data will be generated into two new files:
data_training.xlsx and  data_testing.xlsx or
data_training.csv  and  data_testing.csv
and the generated files can be used in a Neural Network process.

Background:
This is by no means a novel Python code for splitting table for Neural Network 
Modelling purpose. Author is sure that there are dedicated library or more 
advanced code out there for this purpose. It started out as a research 
capacity on Neural Network and it just make sense to implement the coding 
knowledge. The Author hope that this would help. 

